"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:1.8.1\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">1.8.1</span> 標題：磚模、磚窰（brick mold, brickkiln）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">經文出處</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">來： מַלְבֵּן</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音譯： malben)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:31\">2SA 12:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:14\">NAM 3:14</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0356_brick_mold.jpg\" alt=\"哈特謝普蘇特（Hatshepsut）神廟地基磚模（埃及）\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">哈特謝普蘇特（Hatshepsut）神廟地基磚模（埃及） (Metropolitan Museum of Art, CC0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>\n          </p>\n<p>\n            <strong>磚模</strong> ：這是一種長方形的木製容器，不是很大，約20–25×10厘米（8–10×4英吋），用來製作形狀和大小完全相同的泥磚（參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.8.2 磚 (brick)&lt;REALIA:1.8.2&gt;</a> ）。</p>\n<p>\n            <strong>磚窰</strong> ：這是一個大型室外烤爐，用來燒磚使其變得堅硬（參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">1.11.1 窰、爐 (smelting furnace, kiln)&lt;REALIA:1.11.1&gt;</a> 中的插圖）。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">用途</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0357_brick.jpg\" alt=\"泥磚（非利士亞實基倫外城門結構的原用泥磚）\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">泥磚（非利士亞實基倫外城門結構的原用泥磚） (© Ian Scott, CC BY-SA 2.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>工人把黏土或其他製磚材料填充在磚模中。待材料定型後，再把磚從模具中脫出並在陽光下曬乾。有些地方會把磚放在磚窰裡面烘烤使其變硬。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻譯</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:31\">2SA 12:31</a> ：希伯來文<em>malben</em> 只是馬索拉學者認為經文有錯誤，所以在頁旁特別註明的一種讀法；不過，這個建議讀法未見於任何古代抄本或譯本中。但是，現有文本也是讀不通的。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Hebrew Old Testament Text Project (UBS)\">HOTTP</abbr> 建議譯作「磚窰」，這是大多數譯本的譯法。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 和<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Contemporary English Version\">CEV</abbr> 譯成“making bricks”（「做磚」），<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Century Version\">NCV</abbr> 譯成“build with bricks”（「用磚建造」），<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New Revised Standard Version (1989)\">NRSV</abbr> 譯成“brickworks”（「砌磚工作」）。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:14\">NAM 3:14</a> ：下文改述自《〈那鴻書〉、〈哈巴谷書〉和〈西番雅書〉手冊》（<em>A Handbook on The Books of Nahum, Habakkuk, and Zephaniah</em> ，第55—56頁）：這節經文的後半部分講述了製磚的各個步驟。前兩個步驟是「走到黏土裡面，踩踏泥漿」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 直譯），指的是用腳踹踏黏土，使其足夠柔軟以便成型。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 沒有採用並列句，只用一個分句來表達做磚的這個環節：「踹泥以製磚。」在黏土足夠柔軟之後，就被放入到磚模裡面。然後，把成型的磚從模具中取出，放在陽光下曬乾。那鴻吩咐尼尼微人「抓住磚模」（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised Standard Version (1952)\">RSV</abbr> 直譯），<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 的表述更加清楚，英文直譯「將磚模準備就緒」。這節經文的後半部分也可以譯成，「踩踏用來製磚的黏土，並準備磚模」，或「用你的腳使製磚所用的黏土變得柔軟，並準備磚模」。</p>\n<p>另參<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">3.20.1 鋪道、石板地、鋪石地、鋪華石處 (pavement, The Pavement)&lt;REALIA:3.20.1&gt;</a> 中的討論。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
